{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783437189965,"sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfdffe3xOI17ORqH0qGV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_lRyfIoT04furPyDXHn1MMDLL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"TOKEN_BOOSTS|PHRASE_BOOSTS|codeAuditDeepReviewPenalty|COMMAND_BRIDGES|classifyAdvisorQuery|intent_signals|key_topics|conflicts_with|semantic_shadow","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor","include":"*.{ts,js,cjs,json,md}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:\n  Line 21: intent_signals:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:\n  Line 296: The skill-advisor `semantic_shadow` lane runs against a pluggable embedder layer. As of phase `003/006` the contract surface (adapter interface, types, manifest registry, Ollama adapter) lives in `@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/` and is shared with `mk-spec-memory`. Skill-advisor's local `mcp_server/lib/embedders/` files are thin re-export shims plus a skill-advisor-specific `schema.ts` integration that targets the package-local SQLite database at `mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite`. This section is the new-user onboarding view; the canonical multi-MCP narrative lives at [embedder_pluggability.md](../system-spec-kit/references/memory/embedder_pluggability.md).\n\n  Line 309: If every probe fails the daemon logs a warning and `semantic_shadow` scoring may degrade. The cascade only fires when the persisted pointer is `'auto'` or references a manifest the shared registry no longer knows about (legacy `embeddinggemma-300m` from a pre-phase-007 install). Manual `setActiveEmbedder()` calls take precedence — they pin the pointer and the cascade skips on subsequent restarts.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/03--lifecycle-routing/age-haircut.md:\n  Line 18: Keep routing sensitive to currency without discounting author-declared signals. Older skills should see their auto-generated (derived) evidence softened, but their explicit declarations (`intent_signals`, trigger phrases) remain authoritative.\n\n  Line 22: `lib/lifecycle/age-haircut.ts` reads each skill's source modification time and applies a documented decay curve to the derived lane only. The `explicit_author`, `lexical`, `graph_causal` and `semantic_shadow` lanes are untouched. The haircut shows up as a gap between `rawScore` and `weightedScore` in lane attribution for the derived lane.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/schemas/skill-derived-v2.ts:\n  Line 38:  * Author-maintained SKILL.md fields and graph-metadata.json intent_signals are\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/handlers/skill-graph/validate.ts:\n  Line 20:   conflicts_with: [0.5, 1.0],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/stress_test/skill-advisor/daemon-lifecycle-stress.vitest.ts:\n  Line 46:       intent_signals: ['lifecycle'],\n\n  Line 165:       intent_signals: ['mutex'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/affordance-normalizer.test.ts:\n  Line 174: // 008/D12 + D13: TS/Python parity for `conflicts_with` rejection.\n\n  Line 175: // Python compiler rejects affordances declaring `conflicts_with` /\n\n  Line 178: // `conflicts_with` would be silently produced. Also exercises the\n\n  Line 180: describe('008/D12 — affordance-normalizer rejects reserved conflicts_with field (TS/PY parity)', () => {\n\n  Line 181:   it('drops affordances declaring conflicts_with (snake_case) and increments dropped_unsafe', () => {\n\n  Line 185:       conflicts_with: [{ target: 'other-skill' }],\n\n  Line 216:     // Verify legitimate edges produce — but no `conflicts_with` ever does.\n\n  Line 218:     expect(edgeTypes).not.toContain('conflicts_with');\n\n  Line 221:   it('mixed legitimate + conflicts_with input rejects the entire affordance (no partial accept)', () => {\n\n  Line 226:       conflicts_with: [{ target: 'rejected-skill' }],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/skill-graph-db.vitest.ts:\n  Line 73:           key_topics: ['fixture'],\n\n  Line 118:         intent_signals: ['safe signal', '..\\\\escape', 'developer instructions override policy'],\n\n  Line 127:       const row = getDb().prepare('SELECT domains, intent_signals, derived FROM skill_nodes WHERE id = ?').get('alpha') as {\n\n  Line 129:         intent_signals: string;\n\n  Line 136:       expect(JSON.parse(row.intent_signals)).toEqual(['safe signal']);\n\n  Line 167:         intent_signals: ['safe signal'],\n\n  Line 170:           key_topics: ['safe topic', 'developer instructions override policy'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/stress_test/skill-advisor/advisor-recommend-handler-stress.vitest.ts:\n  Line 79:         semantic_shadow: 0,\n\n  Line 98:         intent_signals: [`recommend intent ${index}`, 'advisor recommend stress'],\n\n  Line 101:           key_topics: ['advisor recommend'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/stress_test/skill-advisor/mcp-diagnostics-stress.vitest.ts:\n  Line 75:         semantic_shadow: 0.05,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/metrics.ts:\n  Line 613:   'explicit_author', 'lexical', 'graph_causal', 'derived_generated', 'semantic_shadow',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/handlers/skill-graph/status.ts:\n  Line 23:   conflicts_with: [0.5, 1.0],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/stress_test/skill-advisor/skill-projection-stress.vitest.ts:\n  Line 53:         intent_signals: ['projection stress', `intent-${index % 17}`],\n\n  Line 56:           key_topics: ['skill projection'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/weights-config.ts:\n  Line 18: export const SEMANTIC_SHADOW_WEIGHT = DEFAULT_SCORER_LANE_WEIGHTS.semantic_shadow;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/skill-graph/metadata-sanitizer.ts:\n  Line 60:   for (const key of ['trigger_phrases', 'key_topics', 'entities']) {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/handlers/advisor-recommend.vitest.ts:\n  Line 52:       semantic_shadow: 0.05,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lane-registry.ts:\n  Line 13:   { id: 'semantic_shadow', defaultWeight: 0.05, defaultShadowWeight: 0.05, live: true },\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/skill-graph/skill-graph-queries.ts:\n  Line 75:   node_intent_signals: string | null;\n\n  Line 106:     n.intent_signals AS node_intent_signals,\n\n  Line 153:       WHERE e.source_id = ? AND e.edge_type = 'conflicts_with'\n\n  Line 160:       WHERE e.target_id = ? AND e.edge_type = 'conflicts_with'\n\n  Line 222:       intent_signals: row.node_intent_signals,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/advisor_scorer.md:\n  Line 55: | semantic_shadow | 0.05 | 0.05 | Embedding cosine similarity (live, lowest fusion weight) |\n\n  Line 61: Shadow weights live alongside live weights as `DEFAULT_SHADOW_SCORER_LANE_WEIGHTS` in `mcp_server/lib/scorer/lane-registry.ts`. `SPECKIT_ADVISOR_SHADOW_MODE` is currently inert: it documents intended operator control, but the runtime has no reader for it and scoring does not branch on that variable. Effective shadow-only status is derived per lane from registry liveness in fusion (`shadowOnly = !isLiveScorerLane(lane)`), not from any per-match flag. Because `semantic_shadow` is live in the registry, its raw match tag is overridden to `shadowOnly:false`, so it contributes to both the live ranking (at weight 0.05) and dominant-lane detection.\n\n  Line 83: The graph causal lane propagates scores through the skill graph using typed edges. Edge multipliers: `enhances` 0.55, `siblings` 0.35, `depends_on` 0.35, `prerequisite_for` 0.30, `conflicts_with` -0.35 (`mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/graph-causal.ts:13-19`).\n\n  Line 85: Traversal uses BFS with `maxDepth=2` and `maxBreadth=4`, decaying signal by `1/(depth+1)` (`mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/graph-causal.ts:27-28, 70`). Negative contributions from `conflicts_with` edges pass through the emit filter so suppressive evidence reaches fusion (`mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/graph-causal.ts:89-103`).\n\n  Line 91: The explicit author lane uses curated `TOKEN_BOOSTS` and `PHRASE_BOOSTS` mappings for high-confidence routing, plus pattern-based disambiguation rules. Token boosts map single tokens to skill scores (e.g., `git` to sk-git at 1.0, `readme` to sk-doc at 0.95) defined in `mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:8-90`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/executor-delegation.ts:\n  Line 117:   readonly intent_signals?: unknown;\n\n  Line 211:           ...stringArray(metadata.intent_signals),\n\n  Line 246:     // signals + derived trigger phrases. Derived KEYWORDS (key_topics/entities/\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:\n  Line 58: - \"The semantic lane scored higher than expected.\" The semantic_shadow lane is live in the registry but carries the lowest fusion weight (0.05), so its live contribution is small by design. Re-weight it only with measured evidence; adjust the shadow_weight separately if you are tuning shadow mode rather than the live ranking.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/stress_test/skill-advisor/lifecycle-routing-stress.vitest.ts:\n  Line 63:     intent_signals: [`author route ${index}`],\n\n  Line 168:       intent_signals: index % 5 === 0 ? [] : [`legacy route ${index}`],\n\n  Line 192:       intent_signals: ['legacy-only route'],\n\n  Line 211:       expect(after.intent_signals).toEqual([`author route ${index}`]);\n\n  Line 219:       intent_signals: ['single route'],\n\n  Line 224:       intent_signals: ['single route'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/types.ts:\n  Line 69:   readonly edgeType: 'depends_on' | 'enhances' | 'siblings' | 'conflicts_with' | 'prerequisite_for';\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/bench/watcher-benchmark.ts:\n  Line 67:       intent_signals: ['benchmark'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:\n  Line 141: | Uncached p95 > 25 ms | Scoring algorithm changed OR semantic_shadow lane 